result.execSummary:
The defendant Quinton Nathan Price was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. On one or more other charges, Quinton Nathan Price was found not guilty. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Quinton Nathan Price is presumed innocent of the not guilty charges.

  • Quinton Nathan Price was found guilty of Felon Possess Firearm, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2)(a).
  • Quinton Nathan Price was found guilty of Felon Possess Firearm, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2)(a).
  • Quinton Nathan Price was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Defendant Quinton Nathan Price in court with attorney Eric m Hailstock.  Defendant Quinton Nathan Price in custody.  Marissa Luz Santiago appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Presentence Investigation reviewed.  Statements by state, defense and defendant.   Additional statements by Kila P.
AS to counts 1 and 2, concurrent with each other:    The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 87 MONTHS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, credit for 77 days time served.  CONFINEMENT of 47 MONTHS  and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 40 MONTHS with the following conditions:
-The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and those ordered in count 4, be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.
-Pay all costs, assessments and victim/witness surcharges.
-Provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs; DNA surcharge.
The defendant is advised as a convicted felon he may not carry or possess any firearms/body armor.
The court advises the defendant that voting privileges are suspended during the length of this sentence.
The defendant is given a written explanation of the determinate sentence, and advised of his appeal rights by defense counsel.
The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.   
The defendant is eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.   
AS to count 4:   The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 5 months in the House of Correction, concurrent with counts 1 and 2 with credit for 77 days time served.    The court orders defendant to pay all applicable costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, provide DNA and pay costs as a condition of extended supervision as imposed in counts 1 and 2 and failure to do so will result in entry of civil judgment.
Defendant remanded.

Defendant Quinton Nathan Price in court with attorney Eric M. Hailstock.  Marissa Luz Santiago appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case recalled at 1:10pm.  Court conducts colloquy with defendant as to his decision not to testify in his own behalf and finds it to be a free, knowing and voluntary decision.  Jury in the box at 1:15pm.  Sworn for the defense:  Kila P.  Defense rests.  State will not be providing any rebuttal testimony.  Testimony closed.  Jury out of the box at 1:25pm.  Jury instructions placed on the record and stipulated to by counsels and defendant.  Jury in the box at 1:40pm.  
Court instructed jury.  Closing arguments by state and defense.  Rebuttal argument by the state.  Court charged the jury.  Alternate juror selected by lot (# 1  ) and released.  Jury retired at the hour of 2:20pm to deliberate in the charge of Sheriff's Deputies Baker and Spottek  who were duly sworn for that purpose.  
At the hour of 2:50pm the jury returned and, by their foreperson (#10), brought in verdicts as follows:
Count 1:  Possession of Firearm by a Felon:  GUILTY
Count 2:  Possession of Firearm by a Felon:  GUILTY
Count 3:  Keeping a Drug House, PTAC, Use of a Dangerous Weapon:  NOT GUILTY
Count 4:  Possession of THC:  GUILTY
Court polled and discharged the jury.  Verdicts received and filed.  Court granted state's motion for judgment on the verdicts and denied defense motion for judgments not withstanding the verdicts.  Court ordered entry of judgments of conviction  as to counts 1,2,4 and judgment of acquittal as to count 3.
Upon motion of the state the court will remand the defendant pending sentencing and will order a PSI.  Case adjourned to 6-28-2016 at 8:15 for sentencing.

  Sentencing hearing scheduled for June 28, 2016 at 08:15 am.

Jury out of the box at 10:37am.  Jury in the box at 11:05am.  Sworn for the state:  Laura Hedden-WI State Crime Lab-Controlled Substance Unit; PO Eric Rom (MPD).  State rests subject to rebuttal.  Court excuses jury for lunch and directed to return at 1:10pm.
